<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7147473>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Pethia dikhuensis (A) Holotype, ZSI/APRC/V/P-1961, male, 44.3 mm SL, freshly preserved, (B) Paratype, ZSI/ APRC/V/P-1962, male, 45.4 mm SL (C) Paratype, ZSI/APRC/V/P-1962, female, 45.6 mm SL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7147473/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7147475>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Pethia dikhuensis, in life (A) Holotype, ZSI/APRC/V/P-1961, male, 44.3 mm SL, freshly preserved (B) Paratype, ZSI/APRC/V/P-1962, female, 44.5 mm SL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7147475/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7147477>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Pethia dikhuensis, CIARI/FF-70, 43.0 mm SL, (A) Last unbranched dorsal-fin ray (arrow), (B) Caudal skeleton. Abbreviations: CC, compound centrum; Ep, epural; H1–6, hypurals 1–6; Ph, parhypural; Pls, pleurostyle; PU2, PU3, preural centra 2, 3." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7147477/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7147479>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Pethia dikhuensis, CIARI/FF-70, 43.0 mm SL, (A) Left dentary, lateral view, (B) left premaxilla, dorso-lateral view, (C) left maxilla, lateral view, (D) Fifth ceratobranchial, right side in lateral view and (E) Left infraorbital series, lateral view.Ana, anguloarticular; Cm, coronomeckelian; De, dentary; MC, Meckel’s cartilage; Ra, retroarticular; PP, palatine process; IO1–5, infraorbitals 1–5; So, supraorbital." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7147479/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7147481>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitat at the type locality of Pethia dikhuensis at Dikhu River, 26°17’.9220”N, 94°35’.4300”E, Mokochung District, Nagaland, India." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7147481/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7147485>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Phylogenetic position of Pethia dikhuensis based on the maximum likelihood analysis of the cox1 gene. Values along the nodes are percent bootstraps for 1000 iterations. Blue circle along the name of the taxa denotes the GenBank accession number for the sequences generated in the present study and red circle indicate misidentified sequence from Barman et al. (2018)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7147485/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

